SIMPLE: instruct
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Instruct
<hw>In*struct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>instructus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>instruere</ets> to furnish,
provide, construct, instruct; pref. <ets>in-</ets> in, on +
<ets>struere</ets>. See <er>Structure</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Arranged; furnished; provided.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧He
had neither ship <xex>instruct</xex> with oars, nor men.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Chapman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Instructed; taught; enlightened.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instruct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Instruct
<hw>In*struct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Instructed</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Instructing</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To put in order; to form; to prepare.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They speak to the merits of a cause, after the proctor has
prepared and <qex>instructed</qex> the same for a hearing.</q>
<rj><qau>Ayliffe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To form by communication of knowledge; to inform the
mind of; to impart knowledge or information to; to enlighten; to teach;
to discipline.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Schoolmasters will I keep within my house,⟦br⟧
Fit to <qex>instruct</qex> her youth.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To furnish with directions; to advise; to direct; to
command; <as>as, the judge <ex>instructs</ex> the jury</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>She, being before <qex>instructed</qex> of her mother, said, Give
me here John Baptist's head in a charger.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. xiv.
8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take her in; <qex>instruct</qex> her what she has to do.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To teach; educate; inform; train; discipline;
indoctrinate; direct; enjoin.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Instructer</ent>⟦br⟧
